          <h2>What is BMI?</h2>
          <p>Body Mass Index (BMI) is a measure that uses your height and weight to estimate whether your weight is healthy. It is calculated by dividing your weight in kg by your height in metres squared. A BMI between 18.5 and 24.9 is considered normal.</p>
