          <details>
            <summary>Is BMI accurate?</summary>
            <p>BMI is a useful screening tool but does not measure body fat directly. Very muscular people may have a high BMI without excess fat. For a complete assessment consult a doctor.</p>
          </details>
          <details>
            <summary>What is a healthy BMI?</summary>
            <p>A BMI between 18.5 and 24.9 is considered healthy for most adults. Below 18.5 is underweight and above 25 is overweight.</p>
          </details>
          <details>
            <summary>How is BMI calculated?</summary>
            <p>BMI = weight (kg) ÷ height² (m). For example, a person weighing 70 kg and 1.75 m tall has a BMI of 70 ÷ (1.75 × 1.75) = 22.9.</p>
