      <h2 style="font-family:var(--font-display);font-size:1.3rem;font-weight:700;margin-bottom:1rem">About the BMI Calculator</h2>
      <p style="color:var(--muted);font-size:0.95rem;line-height:1.8;margin-bottom:1rem">The Body Mass Index (BMI) calculator is one of the most widely used tools in medicine and nutrition to quickly assess whether a person's weight is appropriate for their height. It was developed by Belgian mathematician Adolphe Quetelet in the 19th century and has been the standard screening tool used by healthcare professionals worldwide ever since.</p>
      <p style="color:var(--muted);font-size:0.95rem;line-height:1.8;margin-bottom:1rem">Our free BMI calculator gives you an instant result with no registration required. Simply enter your weight in kilograms and your height in centimetres to get your BMI value and find out which category you fall into according to the World Health Organization (WHO) guidelines.</p>
      <p style="color:var(--muted);font-size:0.95rem;line-height:1.8">While BMI is a useful tool, it does have limitations. It does not account for muscle mass, bone density, age or ethnic differences. Athletes and very muscular people may have a high BMI without excess body fat. Always consult a healthcare professional for a complete health assessment.</p>
